# Going back to 1st Principles

As Elon Musk puts it: 
> Well, I do think there’s a good framework for thinking. It is physics. You know, the sort of first principles reasoning. Generally I think there are — what I mean by that is, boil things down to their fundamental truths and reason up from there, as opposed to reasoning by analogy.
Through most of our life, we get through life by reasoning by analogy, which essentially means copying what other people do with slight variations.

# Fundamentals, Fundamentals and well... Fundamentals

Having strong fundamentals in Math IS a pre-requisite to success. If you are working 
on the field of perception, that means having at least an intuitive understanding of trigonometry, 
being comfortable with linear algebra ...

